originalText.text:
I've been to this place few times and it's either hit or miss depending on who will happen to be your nail tech.
From my very recent visit I decided to never go back as the person doing my nails seemed like she had no clue what she was doing and couldn't understand a word in English.
The service is rushed to the point where another tech joins and starts working on the other hand which is pretty weird and inappropriate.

This neighbourhood definitely has better nail salons so go somewhere else.

originalText.text:
I came here hoping for a higher class and quality nail salon but I was mistaken. I asked for the chrome gel manicure, I was told upfront it was $80. It’s a steep price tag (a nail salon downtown charges $50 for the same service) but I was happy to pay the price but with the expectation the service would be equivalent to the price. After patiently waiting 10 mins for the technician, she started with me all frazzled and rushing. No one should use an e-file if they do not receive the proper training on how to use them.  I have one at home that I use for my own cuticles and never damage my nails in the process. She started filing down my nails at the nail bed instead of the cuticle which was hurting me. She told me I needed to relax and I asked her to please only lift and file the cuticle, NOT my nail.
She continued to proceed so I asked her to use cuticle oil and cuticle cutters and that I was switching to a regular manicure. She proceeded to comment on “how bad” my cuticles were. I took a photo one week later with the damage to my nail.
To make it more annoying, when another technician asked her why the manicure was switched she said “she changed her mind and doesn’t want to pay for the gel.” I didn’t change my mind because of the price, I changed my mind because I didn’t feel it was right for me to pay $80 for someone to ruin my nails. She also did a poor job painting the nails.
Only giving 1 star because I paid for a 10 minute massage and the gentleman who was the masseuse was exceptional. He should start his own business, I would see him on a regular basis.

originalText.text: After searching for over a year, I have finally found my new place! I never post reviews, but I had to because of how amazing my dip manicure turned out! Erika was so detailed, have not seen my nails look so good in ages. Well worth the price, will definitely be returning!

originalText.text:
My new go-to spot for the past few months! I have nail salons much closer to me but I always take the extra walk to get my gel mani here. They are professional, meticulous to detail, and clean- 1 time use files, plastic liners, disinfectant machines etc...
Also, they have a great gel polish line in the yellow bottle with fewer toxins and easy soak off; my nails come out so shiny and don't damage. Well worth the price and experience.
